title: For Sale:  Pistol, 7.62 x 25, Norinco 54, $275.00
postcontent: Norinco Model 54, 7.62X25 semi-auto service pistol. Includes two 8 round magazines, and more than 225 rounds of communist bloc ammo. I can't remember where the ammo was manufactured, but I'm sure the primers are berdan and corrosive. The gun was throughly cleaned and oiled after each range day. This is the Chinese version of the Russian Tokarev, the Model 54-1, which was required to include a thumb safety during the Clinton Administration for importation int the USA. The added thumb safety has long since been removed and discarded.7.62x25 is a powerful round, but hard to find and expensive when you do find it. The pistol is heavy, and of low capacity (8 rounds).
